$2.16 for a large coke and a free grilled turkey, bacon, and cheddar sandwich from Jack in the Box. The sandwich is darn good. I recommend anyone in the vicinity of a Jack in the Box cashing in on this deal. I went to the Storke JITB early to avoid any possible rush from this promotion, and walked right... up to the counter and was out of there in just a few minutes.  The other option is a free deli trio with the purchase of a large drink...guess that'll be dinner tonight :-)

I had a fun day on the boat with my family at Turlock Lake :-)
I hope you have a fantastic day!!!

We got a late start today, but have made the most of it.  Started cooking a tri tip in the crock pot. We went for a long walk on Goleta beach out to where the sea lions hang out on the rocks.  Hit a couple thrift stores for good treasures and to Wendy's to tide us over til dinner.  Came home and Jeanetta mixed up some cheeseball dip and a coconut pound cake while I made us some margaritas (on the second pitcher now).  Life is good :-)

LJ Friends who have been in my Home LJ Friends Who I have been in their home (even though she's still not added me back on here haha) Other LJ Friends who I've met in person So if I didn't miss anyone (and sorry if I did), I have have met 29/46 (63%) of my LJ friends. The rest, our paths just haven't crossed yet :-)

Last night I did a bunch of work on my large music project at home, which included adding about 150 songs to my phone...so I figured a good time for one of these...

Step 1: Put your music player on random.
Step 2: Post the first line(s) from the first 15 songs that play.
Step 3: Post and let everyone guess the song and artist.
Step 4: Strike out the songs when someone guesses correctly.
Step 5: Cheating is discouraged.

<lj-cut text="Name that tune...">

1) <strike>I wanna go back to the island, where the shrimp boats tie up to the pilin'</strike>
Tin Cup Chalice - Jimmy Buffett (<lj user="sharkbait">)

2) <strike>She's got a smile that it seems to me, reminds me of childhood memories</strike>
Sweet Child O' Mine - Guns 'N Roses (<lj user="bella_cheval">)

3) Brushfire fairytales, itsy bitsy diamond wells, big fat hurricanes, yellow bellied given names

4) <strike>I've got some big news, the bank finally came through, and I'm holdin' the keys to a brand new Chevrolet</strike>
Mud on the Tires - Brad Paisley (<lj user="bella_cheval">)

5) <strike>I've got sunshine on a cloudy day</strike>
My Girl - The Temptations  (<lj user="bella_cheval">)

6) Met her at the mercado, she was buying avocados, man... she really turned me on

7) <strike>On a dark desert highway</strike>
Hotel California - The Eagles  (<lj user="khanadasc"> and <lj user="bella_cheval">)

8) <strike>What would you think if I sang out of tune, would you stand up and walk out on me?</strike>
With a Little Help from My Friends - Joe Cocker (<lj user="khanadasc">)

9) <strike>I want my, I want my MTV</strike>
Money for Nothing - Dire Straits (<lj user="bella_cheval">)

10) <strike>Early in the morning, risin' to the street</strike>
What I Got - Sublime (<lj user="captain_phil">)

11) When Im alone in my room sometimes I stare at the wall, and in the back of my mind I hear my conscience call

12) <strike>Well, I know it's kind of late, I hope I didn't wake you, but what I got to say can't wait I know you'd understand</strike>
I'll Have To Say I Love You In A Song - Jim Croce (<lj user="khanadasc">)

13) <strike>You know I was talking to my friend desdemona the other day she runs this space station and bake shop down near boomtown.</strike>
Fruitcakes - Jimmy Buffett (<lj user="sharkbait">)

14) <strike>Do you wanna get rocked?</strike>
Let's Get Rocked - Def Leppard (<lj user="bella_cheval">)

15) <strike>Early one mornin' while makin' the rounds, I took a shot of cocaine and I shot my woman down</strike>
Cocaine Blues - Johnny Cash (<lj user="khanadasc">)

I hope all the Fathers out there have a great Fathers Day! (Ron - Me with Beer - My Dad) And I hope everyone has a fantastic Summer Solstice! Better than me anyway, as I'm at the office working haha.
